1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:40,000
(Watch on www.dramacool.club Support Admin)

2
00:00:42,626 --> 00:00:43,658
[This drama is a work of fiction.]

3
00:00:43,658 --> 00:00:44,697
[Any resemblance to real persons,
places, or events is coincidental.]

4
00:00:44,697 --> 00:00:45,736
[Scenes with child actors and animals
were filmed safely]

5
00:00:45,736 --> 00:00:47,032
[under professional supervision.]

6
00:00:47,881 --> 00:00:51,433
[Nine years prior]

7
00:01:03,125 --> 00:01:04,606
Yes, Director Jo.

8
00:01:04,606 --> 00:01:06,900
Hello, Chief Prosecutor.

9
00:01:06,900 --> 00:01:08,760
How far out are you?

10
00:01:08,760 --> 00:01:11,245
Roughly ten minutes to go.

11
00:01:12,030 --> 00:01:14,491
We're looking at ten minutes or so.

12
00:01:14,491 --> 00:01:15,709
Yes.

13
00:01:15,709 --> 00:01:18,375
It's a fine occasion, so no need to rush.

14
00:01:18,375 --> 00:01:20,129
Yes.

15
00:01:26,253 --> 00:01:28,085
[Episode 4]

16
00:01:37,598 --> 00:01:39,482
I think we've arrived.

17
00:01:43,751 --> 00:01:45,837
I appreciate you making the long trip.

18
00:01:45,837 --> 00:01:48,991
The chairman got here early
and is expecting you.

19
00:01:54,698 --> 00:01:56,374
Right this way.

20
00:02:17,000 --> 00:02:18,563
Hey.

21
00:02:25,729 --> 00:02:27,522
There's no crew in sight.

22
00:02:27,522 --> 00:02:29,783
Is this actually where we're filming today?

23
00:02:29,783 --> 00:02:31,083
Yeah.

24
00:02:31,083 --> 00:02:32,903
If today's filming goes smoothly,

25
00:02:32,903 --> 00:02:37,290
CEO Oh agreed to forget what you pulled on set.

26
00:02:57,552 --> 00:02:59,888
- Over here.
- Yes.

27
00:03:01,250 --> 00:03:02,940
Get over here.

28
00:03:05,584 --> 00:03:07,653
Hey, you head in first.

29
00:03:30,085 --> 00:03:32,595
Oh, you're here?

30
00:03:33,876 --> 00:03:35,882
- Sir.
- Long trip, huh?

31
00:03:35,882 --> 00:03:37,718
Come in.

32
00:03:41,142 --> 00:03:42,848
We're filming today, right?

33
00:03:42,848 --> 00:03:45,608
I didn't see any of the crew.

34
00:03:59,125 --> 00:04:01,074
Sir.

35
00:04:01,074 --> 00:04:03,368
This isn't a shoot, is it?

36
00:04:03,985 --> 00:04:06,671
Something more important.

37
00:04:13,917 --> 00:04:16,046
Chairman, and Chief Prosecutor.

38
00:04:16,046 --> 00:04:17,924
Thank you for your patience.

39
00:04:17,924 --> 00:04:20,343
This is Han Ji Soo,
a new actress I just brought on.

40
00:04:20,343 --> 00:04:26,106
Great voice,
and she really knows how to use her body.

41
00:04:29,876 --> 00:04:32,230
What's the holdup?

42
00:04:32,230 --> 00:04:34,281
Introduce yourself, yeah?

43
00:05:09,122 --> 00:05:11,110
Yes, Chief Prosecutor.

44
00:05:13,834 --> 00:05:15,614
Oh, yes.

45
00:05:17,709 --> 00:05:19,820
Oh, I'll have it there shortly.

46
00:05:19,820 --> 00:05:21,518
Yes.

47
00:05:36,000 --> 00:05:37,587
Somebody help.

48
00:05:37,587 --> 00:05:40,347
Please, somebody help!

49
00:05:46,584 --> 00:05:48,772
What the hell do you think you're doing?

50
00:06:08,410 --> 00:06:10,120
Hey.

51
00:06:10,120 --> 00:06:12,753
Easy there.

52
00:06:12,753 --> 00:06:14,965
You almost hurt her.

53
00:06:16,083 --> 00:06:17,333
Ji Soo,

54
00:06:17,333 --> 00:06:19,546
are you okay?

55
00:06:19,546 --> 00:06:23,928
What is this...

56
00:06:23,928 --> 00:06:27,512
Just stay still. Don't make a scene.

57
00:06:27,512 --> 00:06:29,855
My apologies, Chairman.

58
00:06:38,375 --> 00:06:40,199
It's alright.

59
00:06:58,843 --> 00:07:02,221
Anything else I can get you?

60
00:07:03,149 --> 00:07:05,391
That'll do. Head out.

61
00:07:06,103 --> 00:07:10,938
Okay,
all non-essentials can step out now, please.

62
00:07:12,557 --> 00:07:14,400
Let's go.

63
00:07:50,929 --> 00:07:53,107
I believe

64
00:07:53,107 --> 00:07:56,359
everything fell apart from that night on.

65
00:07:57,226 --> 00:08:01,780
So that's the moment
all these lives got tangled.

66
00:08:02,375 --> 00:08:03,906
But

67
00:08:03,906 --> 00:08:06,285
following that night's events,

68
00:08:07,542 --> 00:08:09,614
Han Ji Soo passed away.

69
00:08:09,614 --> 00:08:13,618
[Actress Han Ji Soo Found Dead at Home]

70
00:08:22,085 --> 00:08:23,625
What are we going to do with Sang Ah?

71
00:08:23,625 --> 00:08:26,143
She hasn't been herself
since the Ji Soo story hit.

72
00:08:26,143 --> 00:08:27,715
Filming's been called off too,

73
00:08:27,715 --> 00:08:30,976
and the reporters out there have us boxed in.

74
00:08:33,250 --> 00:08:34,632
Sang Ah!

75
00:08:34,632 --> 00:08:35,913
Let me call you back.

76
00:08:35,913 --> 00:08:37,267
Where are you going?

77
00:08:37,267 --> 00:08:38,852
Sang Ah!

78
00:09:30,278 --> 00:09:32,375
Sang Ah, wake up!

79
00:09:32,375 --> 00:09:35,791
No more photos! I told you to stop!

80
00:10:07,774 --> 00:10:13,237
[I've made dinner]
[I'll be there soon]

81
00:10:13,237 --> 00:10:18,992
[Why aren't you picking up?
Nothing's wrong, right?]

82
00:10:27,669 --> 00:10:31,578
[I'll take only the good memories with me.
Thank you for everything. Goodbye]

83
00:10:36,756 --> 00:10:39,322
[I'll take only the good memories with me.
Thank you for everything. Goodbye]

84
00:11:15,377 --> 00:11:16,635
Hello.

85
00:11:16,635 --> 00:11:20,430
My name's Park Jae Sang,
and I'll be at your service from today.

86
00:11:20,430 --> 00:11:22,250
Oh Kwang Jae

87
00:11:22,250 --> 00:11:25,607
had been managing Chu Sang Ah's affairs
since she was without an agency,

88
00:11:25,607 --> 00:11:27,778
and following that incident,

89
00:11:28,521 --> 00:11:31,764
he put me on as her personal security.

90
00:11:31,764 --> 00:11:33,992
Security in name only, though,

91
00:11:34,945 --> 00:11:37,834
because with Chu Sang Ah spiraling,

92
00:11:37,834 --> 00:11:40,017
the real job was surveillance.

93
00:11:40,017 --> 00:11:42,292
But I didn't mind.

94
00:11:43,491 --> 00:11:46,709
Once I got out of juvenile hall as a kid,
I had nothing to look forward to.

95
00:11:46,709 --> 00:11:50,917
But Chu Sang Ah was my first love,

96
00:11:50,917 --> 00:11:53,929
and being near her was
the one thing I ever wished for.

97
00:11:57,458 --> 00:11:59,093
And who approved that?

98
00:11:59,093 --> 00:12:02,263
CEO Oh told me to...

99
00:12:02,263 --> 00:12:04,709
I believe she caught on

100
00:12:04,709 --> 00:12:06,058
that I was there to monitor her.

101
00:12:06,058 --> 00:12:07,862
Go away.

102
00:12:12,769 --> 00:12:14,191
Look,

103
00:12:14,191 --> 00:12:16,660
we have to leave immediately...

104
00:12:17,349 --> 00:12:20,490
CEO Oh told me to come get you.

105
00:12:20,490 --> 00:12:22,333
What?

106
00:12:22,333 --> 00:12:25,585
He sent me to take you
to Han Ji Soo's funeral...

107
00:12:46,682 --> 00:12:50,986
[May she find eternal peace]

108
00:13:40,750 --> 00:13:42,688
I'm sorry.

109
00:13:42,688 --> 00:13:46,333
I can't even face you.
I should've taken care of it properly.

110
00:13:59,380 --> 00:14:03,041
Forward the reshoot invoice

111
00:14:03,041 --> 00:14:05,668
and equity agreement to Ji Soo's agency,

112
00:14:05,668 --> 00:14:08,390
and let the director know
Seon Young's replacing Ji Soo.

113
00:14:08,390 --> 00:14:10,524
Understood.

114
00:14:29,507 --> 00:14:31,378
What are you doing?

115
00:14:39,795 --> 00:14:41,680
Murderer.

116
00:14:46,333 --> 00:14:48,687
Ji Soo's dead because of you.

117
00:14:54,500 --> 00:14:56,229
Yeah.

118
00:14:56,229 --> 00:14:58,397
I couldn't keep Ji Soo safe.

119
00:14:58,397 --> 00:15:01,567
You're the reason Ji Soo's gone.

120
00:15:01,567 --> 00:15:04,619
You murdered her!

121
00:15:07,625 --> 00:15:09,833
Are you drunk?

122
00:15:13,625 --> 00:15:16,583
I'm done seeing you fall apart over Ji Soo.

123
00:15:16,583 --> 00:15:18,717
That's it.

124
00:15:19,750 --> 00:15:22,500
What did you do to Ji Soo?

125
00:15:22,500 --> 00:15:26,041
Say it! Answer me! Spit it out!

126
00:15:26,041 --> 00:15:28,052
What did you do to her? Tell me!

127
00:15:28,052 --> 00:15:29,637
- Fuck!
- Let's go.

128
00:15:29,637 --> 00:15:31,180
Let go! You bastard.

129
00:15:31,180 --> 00:15:32,709
- Let go!
- Let's go.

130
00:15:32,709 --> 00:15:34,667
Let go!

131
00:15:34,667 --> 00:15:36,276
Let go!

132
00:15:38,417 --> 00:15:40,322
That's enough.

133
00:15:41,650 --> 00:15:43,275
Wait a second.

134
00:15:43,275 --> 00:15:44,851
You...

135
00:15:47,333 --> 00:15:49,748
Mark my words.

136
00:15:50,333 --> 00:15:53,835
I'll drag you straight to hell.

137
00:16:38,664 --> 00:16:40,477
[Oh Kwang Jae, Kwon Se Myeong]

138
00:16:42,543 --> 00:16:44,386
[Oh Kwang Jae and Kwon Se Myeong,
from partners to sworn brothers]

139
00:16:46,881 --> 00:16:48,447
[Oh Kwang Jae and Kwon Se Myeong first met]

140
00:16:48,447 --> 00:16:49,977
[at the 2016 Hallyu Cultural
Business Agreement Ceremony]

141
00:16:49,977 --> 00:16:52,919
[The two have since become sworn brothers]

142
00:16:54,000 --> 00:16:56,815
Sworn brothers...

143
00:16:57,917 --> 00:17:00,645
Anything else I can get you?

144
00:17:00,645 --> 00:17:02,814
That'll do. Head out.

145
00:17:04,942 --> 00:17:08,952
Okay, all non-essentials
can step out now, please.

146
00:17:19,622 --> 00:17:21,851
[The two have since become sworn brothers]

147
00:17:23,834 --> 00:17:29,787
[Chu Sang Ah, Emotional Spiral and Series of
No-Shows After Han Ji Soo's Death]

148
00:17:31,384 --> 00:17:32,995
[Chu Sang Ah is reportedly in deep shock
following Han Ji Soo's death.]

149
00:18:13,176 --> 00:18:15,595
Once Han Ji Soo passed away,

150
00:18:15,595 --> 00:18:18,344
she began behaving erratically on set,

151
00:18:18,344 --> 00:18:20,965
and on top of that she got an eating disorder
and her health declined,

152
00:18:20,965 --> 00:18:22,984
so Oh Kwang Jae

153
00:18:23,917 --> 00:18:26,488
all but imprisoned her

154
00:18:27,250 --> 00:18:29,366
and began holding her captive.

155
00:20:25,792 --> 00:20:27,328
Hello?

156
00:20:27,328 --> 00:20:29,652
Is this the police?

157
00:20:38,405 --> 00:20:41,831
Word is you visited Lawyer Choi
to ask about the penalty fees.

158
00:20:47,000 --> 00:20:49,130
Oh Kwang Jae,

159
00:20:50,291 --> 00:20:52,212
what the hell have you done to me?

160
00:20:52,212 --> 00:20:54,629
Sang Ah, don't go down this road.

161
00:20:54,629 --> 00:20:55,991
You already know.

162
00:20:55,991 --> 00:20:58,515
There's no getting away from me.

163
00:21:00,426 --> 00:21:02,800
[Oh Kwang Jae]

164
00:21:21,004 --> 00:21:22,578
You're aware there aren't just one

165
00:21:22,578 --> 00:21:25,166
or two files like this on my hard drive, right?

166
00:21:26,786 --> 00:21:29,587
Oh Kwang Jae!

167
00:21:30,873 --> 00:21:32,918
I don't want to push it this far either,

168
00:21:32,918 --> 00:21:35,504
so for now, stay put.

169
00:21:35,504 --> 00:21:37,971
Just remain at home and lie low.

170
00:21:38,673 --> 00:21:40,383
Oh, peek out your window.

171
00:21:40,383 --> 00:21:42,010
Notice who's out there?

172
00:21:42,010 --> 00:21:44,936
If you have to leave, speak to him.

173
00:24:08,977 --> 00:24:11,916
Cut! Okay!

174
00:24:12,786 --> 00:24:14,919
Are you alright?

175
00:24:18,250 --> 00:24:20,883
Prepping for the next scene!

176
00:24:21,584 --> 00:24:23,428
You alright?

177
00:24:54,979 --> 00:24:57,879
What made her into a monster,

178
00:24:58,667 --> 00:25:00,250
at the end of the day,

179
00:25:00,250 --> 00:25:03,009
was Oh Kwang Jae. That's what I figured out.

180
00:25:05,709 --> 00:25:07,972
Let's pause here for a second.

181
00:25:11,417 --> 00:25:12,919
Park Jae Sang,

182
00:25:12,919 --> 00:25:16,195
doesn't something feel wrong to you here?

183
00:25:16,195 --> 00:25:17,200
What do you...

184
00:25:17,200 --> 00:25:20,719
Have you still not sorted out
your feelings for Chu Sang Ah?

185
00:25:20,719 --> 00:25:24,071
This keeps sliding
into Chu Sang Ah coming off as a victim.

186
00:25:24,713 --> 00:25:27,401
If that's how it goes,
it won't fit our thumbnail for today,

187
00:25:27,401 --> 00:25:30,280
and if this goes on air and viewers start
feeling sorry for Chu Sang Ah,

188
00:25:30,280 --> 00:25:32,997
you're the only one
who looks like a psycho stalker.

189
00:25:35,876 --> 00:25:38,292
Anyway,

190
00:25:38,292 --> 00:25:40,293
what's the next issue?

191
00:25:40,293 --> 00:25:42,292
The Oh Kwang Jae files.

192
00:25:42,292 --> 00:25:43,834
The ones I received before?

193
00:25:43,834 --> 00:25:45,426
Yes.

194
00:25:47,711 --> 00:25:51,550
[Oh Kwang Jae's Entertainment List,
Chu Sang Ah]

195
00:25:51,550 --> 00:25:52,969
[Investor, Kwon Se Myeong]

196
00:25:52,969 --> 00:25:55,058
When and where did you say you captured this?

197
00:25:55,058 --> 00:25:56,555
Oh Kwang Jae told me

198
00:25:56,555 --> 00:25:58,807
to pick something up from his office,

199
00:25:58,807 --> 00:26:01,269
and I noticed her name by chance,
so I snapped a picture.

200
00:26:01,269 --> 00:26:03,454
Let's pass on this one.

201
00:26:04,638 --> 00:26:06,697
What else did we have?

202
00:26:08,258 --> 00:26:10,952
Sang Ah almost died,

203
00:26:14,208 --> 00:26:16,499
and you're just going to gloss over that?

204
00:26:20,333 --> 00:26:23,506
This is what made her say she wanted to die,

205
00:26:25,125 --> 00:26:28,177
that the only escape from Oh Kwang Jae

206
00:26:28,899 --> 00:26:31,667
was for one of them to end up dead,

207
00:26:31,667 --> 00:26:33,724
and that's why

208
00:26:35,208 --> 00:26:37,895
she told me to kill him.

209
00:26:47,125 --> 00:26:49,073
Let go!

210
00:26:50,068 --> 00:26:52,285
Let go.

211
00:27:39,201 --> 00:27:40,534
Park Jae Sang.

212
00:27:40,534 --> 00:27:42,183
[Case Summary Report]

213
00:27:42,183 --> 00:27:44,382
You're the suspect arrested at the crime scene.

214
00:27:44,382 --> 00:27:47,542
Then why deny the allegations at this point?

215
00:27:47,542 --> 00:27:50,890
Yes, I went with the intent to kill him.

216
00:27:50,890 --> 00:27:53,221
But I didn't actually do it.

217
00:27:53,221 --> 00:27:55,925
If you insist on denying the charges,

218
00:27:55,925 --> 00:27:59,226
let's change our angle of approach.

219
00:27:59,958 --> 00:28:02,514
So your position is...

220
00:28:02,514 --> 00:28:05,183
Chu Sang Ah, suffering
under the Oh Kwang Jae files,

221
00:28:05,183 --> 00:28:07,333
gave the order to kill him

222
00:28:07,333 --> 00:28:09,019
but you didn't carry it out yourself.

223
00:28:09,019 --> 00:28:10,780
Is that correct?

224
00:28:12,208 --> 00:28:13,898
Yes.

225
00:28:13,898 --> 00:28:15,951
Well, in that case...

226
00:28:19,282 --> 00:28:21,123
Chu Sang Ah.

227
00:28:26,083 --> 00:28:28,375
How did you get dragged

228
00:28:28,375 --> 00:28:31,097
into those files?

229
00:28:31,097 --> 00:28:33,838
I needed to keep the other actresses safe.

230
00:28:33,838 --> 00:28:35,631
And that led you

231
00:28:35,631 --> 00:28:38,630
to commission a killing.

232
00:28:38,630 --> 00:28:40,726
What do you mean by that?

233
00:28:41,678 --> 00:28:43,306
Park Jae Sang insists

234
00:28:43,306 --> 00:28:47,984
that you ordered Oh Kwang Jae's murder.

235
00:28:51,625 --> 00:28:53,698
Is there any truth to that?

236
00:28:54,557 --> 00:28:56,492
I'll admit

237
00:28:57,083 --> 00:29:00,287
I wished Oh Kwang Jae
would simply cease to exist.

238
00:29:01,185 --> 00:29:04,458
So I'm not able to completely deny it.

239
00:29:07,167 --> 00:29:09,714
But let me ask you, Prosecutor.

240
00:29:11,541 --> 00:29:15,962
Has there never been a person you wanted

241
00:29:15,962 --> 00:29:18,389
to just vanish from your life?

242
00:29:20,041 --> 00:29:21,934
With all your heart.

243
00:29:31,476 --> 00:29:34,000
But I didn't ask

244
00:29:34,000 --> 00:29:36,574
for him to be killed.

245
00:29:40,113 --> 00:29:42,198
She told me

246
00:29:42,198 --> 00:29:45,624
she hoped Oh Kwang Jae would die.

247
00:29:48,917 --> 00:29:52,339
I asked whether she commissioned his killing.

248
00:29:54,458 --> 00:29:56,552
Commissioned...

249
00:30:03,958 --> 00:30:05,686
Darn it.

250
00:30:08,098 --> 00:30:09,810
Did Chu Sang Ah

251
00:30:09,810 --> 00:30:12,234
offer money or anything

252
00:30:13,000 --> 00:30:15,273
to officially contract you

253
00:30:15,273 --> 00:30:18,491
to take his life?

254
00:30:19,750 --> 00:30:22,077
That's the question here.

255
00:30:27,911 --> 00:30:29,668
Sang Ah.

256
00:30:33,750 --> 00:30:35,633
Sang Ah.

257
00:30:49,667 --> 00:30:50,892
Sang Ah!

258
00:30:50,892 --> 00:30:53,375
Sang Ah.

259
00:30:53,375 --> 00:30:56,000
Please wake up.

260
00:30:56,000 --> 00:30:58,072
Please.

261
00:30:59,191 --> 00:31:02,821
Sang Ah. Open your eyes. Please?

262
00:31:03,958 --> 00:31:07,039
Sang Ah, please.

263
00:31:10,120 --> 00:31:12,795
Just hold on a second.

264
00:31:17,084 --> 00:31:20,250
If they take me to the ER now,

265
00:31:20,250 --> 00:31:23,590
it hits the press instantly. You get that?

266
00:31:23,590 --> 00:31:26,178
Are you really that clueless?

267
00:31:27,834 --> 00:31:29,812
I'm sorry.

268
00:31:53,747 --> 00:31:56,584
You should've just

269
00:31:56,584 --> 00:31:59,758
let me die like this.

270
00:32:01,792 --> 00:32:03,822
Why did you...

271
00:32:07,208 --> 00:32:10,603
The truth is, I wanted to live.

272
00:32:12,125 --> 00:32:15,274
All I wanted was a normal life.

273
00:32:16,958 --> 00:32:20,321
There's no end to this

274
00:32:21,815 --> 00:32:25,182
unless one of us dies.

275
00:32:39,542 --> 00:32:41,217
Sang Ah.

276
00:32:45,333 --> 00:32:47,932
I'll keep you safe.

277
00:32:52,247 --> 00:32:54,855
Tell me what I should do.

278
00:33:03,917 --> 00:33:07,952
You know my mother died when I was little.

279
00:33:10,348 --> 00:33:13,040
I've lived on my own all this time.

280
00:33:16,517 --> 00:33:19,380
If that man were simply gone,

281
00:33:23,163 --> 00:33:26,428
we could have a life together.

282
00:33:45,667 --> 00:33:47,449
I...

283
00:33:50,996 --> 00:33:53,664
I want to be your woman.

284
00:33:59,922 --> 00:34:02,339
My entire future

285
00:34:03,709 --> 00:34:06,051
is yours.

286
00:34:12,302 --> 00:34:14,601
So, Jae Sang...

287
00:34:21,458 --> 00:34:24,236
Will you kill Oh Kwang Jae for me?

288
00:34:35,500 --> 00:34:37,775
A few days after, tidying her apartment,

289
00:34:37,775 --> 00:34:40,686
I came across a bug Oh Kwang Jae had hidden.

290
00:34:40,686 --> 00:34:42,415
So I took it out.

291
00:34:42,415 --> 00:34:44,271
This particular recording will be revealed

292
00:34:44,271 --> 00:34:46,667
in Part Two.

293
00:34:46,667 --> 00:34:49,254
Oh Kwang Jae was brutal, no doubt.

294
00:34:49,254 --> 00:34:52,511
But Chu Sang Ah weaponized her pain

295
00:34:52,511 --> 00:34:55,834
and played Mr. Park while putting on an act.

296
00:34:55,834 --> 00:34:58,763
She really is an actress through and through.

297
00:34:58,763 --> 00:34:59,876
Anyway,

298
00:34:59,876 --> 00:35:01,307
Park Jae Sang.

299
00:35:01,307 --> 00:35:04,855
Why not make that recording public back then?

300
00:35:04,855 --> 00:35:08,030
I trusted the word she gave me.

301
00:35:09,255 --> 00:35:11,116
Which one?

302
00:35:12,054 --> 00:35:15,329
That she'd stay with me after my release.

303
00:35:17,200 --> 00:35:19,325
But the moment I learned she betrayed that vow

304
00:35:19,325 --> 00:35:21,574
[Choi Ji Ho's Fact Check]

305
00:35:21,574 --> 00:35:24,797
and wed Bang Tae Seop,

306
00:35:25,584 --> 00:35:27,591
that's when I decided.

307
00:35:28,601 --> 00:35:31,303
I'd put this recording out there

308
00:35:32,652 --> 00:35:36,266
[Choi Ji Ho's Fact Check]
and reveal who they truly are.

309
00:36:02,452 --> 00:36:04,623
I listened to that recording.

310
00:36:05,538 --> 00:36:09,169
You should've warned me
that thing was out there.

311
00:36:12,584 --> 00:36:14,972
I had no idea it existed either.

312
00:36:16,397 --> 00:36:20,018
I took care of the USB, but a duplicate exists.

313
00:36:21,096 --> 00:36:23,630
If that surfaces, it's over for us.

314
00:36:23,630 --> 00:36:28,026
Your return to acting, my party nomination,
everything falls apart.

315
00:36:29,041 --> 00:36:31,864
Do you know what I sacrificed
to reach this point?

316
00:36:35,000 --> 00:36:37,320
What made you do it?

317
00:36:37,320 --> 00:36:39,580
There was no need to take it that far.

318
00:36:41,375 --> 00:36:43,917
When Ji Soo ended up like that,

319
00:36:44,625 --> 00:36:47,129
I lost my mind completely.

320
00:36:48,248 --> 00:36:51,400
Oh Kwang Jae turned my life into a nightmare.

321
00:36:51,400 --> 00:36:53,046
You know it!

322
00:36:53,046 --> 00:36:56,263
If he didn't die, I was the one who would!

323
00:37:07,964 --> 00:37:10,569
Even without what you did,

324
00:37:13,375 --> 00:37:15,657
Oh Kwang Jae still would've ended up dead.

325
00:37:21,625 --> 00:37:23,790
What is that supposed to mean?

326
00:37:26,417 --> 00:37:28,397
Whenever Oh Kwang Jae

327
00:37:28,397 --> 00:37:30,289
hosted big names,

328
00:37:30,289 --> 00:37:32,291
[Kwon Se Myeong, Oh Kwang Jae, Chu Sang Ah]
he'd have actresses accompany them.

329
00:37:32,291 --> 00:37:34,296
Testimonies from those actresses

330
00:37:34,296 --> 00:37:36,167
along with a document listing their names,

331
00:37:36,167 --> 00:37:40,466
he held onto it all as proof.

332
00:37:40,466 --> 00:37:41,828
To use as blackmail material.

333
00:37:41,828 --> 00:37:43,332
Exactly.

334
00:37:43,332 --> 00:37:47,098
That's why Oh Kwang Jae was out there

335
00:37:47,098 --> 00:37:49,617
boasting that cash would roll in soon enough.

336
00:37:49,617 --> 00:37:51,958
And one more thing.

337
00:37:51,958 --> 00:37:56,000
Here are the bloodstain test findings

338
00:37:56,000 --> 00:37:58,075
from the Seogwang Hotel murder scene.

339
00:38:01,195 --> 00:38:06,417
[The unidentified individual
is presumed to be Lim Kwang Sung]

340
00:38:06,417 --> 00:38:09,044
A hired assassination...

341
00:38:20,089 --> 00:38:24,471
Kwon Se Myeong, under pressure
from Oh Kwang Jae,

342
00:38:24,471 --> 00:38:27,688
commissioned the killing.

343
00:39:08,471 --> 00:39:12,364
[To Lim Kwang Sung, Motor Vehicle Tax Bill]

344
00:40:29,584 --> 00:40:34,700
[K Pictures CEO Oh Kwang Jae,
entered Room 408, 3 AM, the 13th]

345
00:41:15,473 --> 00:41:19,435
[Print 1, Print 2, Print 3, Print 4]

346
00:41:19,435 --> 00:41:24,117
[Fingerprint Subject, Jo Chang Min,
Matches Latent Print 1]

347
00:41:41,541 --> 00:41:43,629
Bang Tae Seop.

348
00:41:44,966 --> 00:41:47,304
You recognize these faces, don't you?

349
00:41:50,427 --> 00:41:51,759
No, sir.

350
00:41:51,759 --> 00:41:53,638
You were present. You saw them that evening.

351
00:41:53,638 --> 00:41:55,506
I'm not sure what you mean.

352
00:41:55,506 --> 00:41:57,314
I'm sorry.

353
00:41:59,542 --> 00:42:01,626
Good.

354
00:42:01,626 --> 00:42:03,938
All that you witnessed and heard that night?

355
00:42:03,938 --> 00:42:05,246
Nothing.

356
00:42:05,246 --> 00:42:07,594
I didn't see a thing. I didn't hear a thing.

357
00:42:07,594 --> 00:42:10,361
Exactly. You stayed home that evening.

358
00:42:10,361 --> 00:42:13,955
You first heard of him from news reports.

359
00:42:21,208 --> 00:42:23,673
This hits the papers tomorrow morning.

360
00:42:25,334 --> 00:42:31,913
["Film mogul Oh Kwang Jae killed
by Chu Sang Ah's bodyguard."]

361
00:42:34,761 --> 00:42:36,834
The suspect was apprehended on the spot.

362
00:42:36,834 --> 00:42:39,710
Why keep digging any further?

363
00:42:39,710 --> 00:42:41,684
Push this any harder

364
00:42:41,684 --> 00:42:45,510
and we only drag out connections
no one needs revealed.

365
00:42:45,510 --> 00:42:47,280
Sir.

366
00:42:48,883 --> 00:42:51,458
You should be heading to Special Division now.

367
00:42:51,458 --> 00:42:53,161
Isn't that so?

368
00:43:30,107 --> 00:43:33,030
[Based on all evidence, Chairman Kwon]

369
00:43:33,030 --> 00:43:35,203
[Se Myeong, via his director of staff...]

370
00:44:09,274 --> 00:44:10,984
Park Jae Sang got there before anyone

371
00:44:10,984 --> 00:44:13,992
yet only succeeded in attempted murder.

372
00:44:22,993 --> 00:44:26,834
Based on all gathered evidence,

373
00:44:26,834 --> 00:44:28,333
Chairman Kwon Se Myeong, through his director,

374
00:44:28,333 --> 00:44:32,385
directed Mr. Lim to murder Oh Kwang Jae.

375
00:44:37,750 --> 00:44:40,177
Mr. Lim showed up moments later

376
00:44:40,177 --> 00:44:42,888
and drove a blade into Oh Kwang Jae twice.

377
00:44:42,888 --> 00:44:46,110
Forensic evidence supports this conclusion.

378
00:44:47,292 --> 00:44:49,413
Without question,

379
00:44:49,413 --> 00:44:54,407
this is a hit commissioned by Chairman Kwon.

380
00:44:56,360 --> 00:44:57,754
[Print]

381
00:45:07,454 --> 00:45:11,766
[Criminal Case Records]

382
00:45:59,575 --> 00:46:03,101
We don't really have reason to meet, do we?

383
00:46:07,350 --> 00:46:11,526
This is evidence from the Oh Kwang Jae scene.

384
00:46:12,275 --> 00:46:16,565
His phone led us to two additional hard drives.

385
00:46:16,565 --> 00:46:22,029
Years' worth of footage, images, and audio.

386
00:46:22,029 --> 00:46:24,834
We pulled hundreds of files from them.

387
00:46:24,834 --> 00:46:26,468
What I brought here

388
00:46:26,468 --> 00:46:30,086
are strictly the files connected to you.

389
00:46:35,155 --> 00:46:37,218
So what did you think?

390
00:46:38,441 --> 00:46:40,513
Was it entertaining for you?

391
00:46:43,417 --> 00:46:45,437
Typically, evidence in a case is restricted

392
00:46:45,437 --> 00:46:48,405
to law enforcement and investigators.

393
00:46:48,405 --> 00:46:51,524
It's stored within the prosecution's office.

394
00:46:52,667 --> 00:46:54,975
However, this particular material,

395
00:46:54,975 --> 00:46:58,073
I'm prepared to put it all on the line

396
00:46:59,015 --> 00:47:01,493
to make it disappear on my own.

397
00:47:06,872 --> 00:47:08,709
Why would you do that?

398
00:47:08,709 --> 00:47:11,203
Because I understand what all of it represents.

399
00:47:11,203 --> 00:47:14,834
I know what it cost you to reach this point.

400
00:47:14,834 --> 00:47:16,758
All of it.

401
00:47:22,208 --> 00:47:24,311
Even now that Oh Kwang Jae is dead,

402
00:47:24,311 --> 00:47:28,372
others like Han Ji Soo will keep appearing.

403
00:47:28,372 --> 00:47:30,855
I'd like to prevent that from happening.

404
00:47:33,167 --> 00:47:36,528
That's a bold thing to say to a woman.

405
00:47:38,951 --> 00:47:41,282
Is that the card you're playing?

406
00:47:43,584 --> 00:47:46,667
It's an offer that serves you well.

407
00:47:46,667 --> 00:47:48,373
We see

408
00:47:49,578 --> 00:47:53,378
ourselves in those like us.

409
00:47:57,375 --> 00:47:59,384
Yeah, you're right.

410
00:48:00,591 --> 00:48:02,679
Most people wouldn't understand,

411
00:48:03,375 --> 00:48:05,515
but you do.

412
00:48:07,757 --> 00:48:11,062
You've seen everything

413
00:48:11,933 --> 00:48:14,065
I had to do to survive.

414
00:48:18,458 --> 00:48:20,051
I built my life

415
00:48:20,051 --> 00:48:22,956
over Han Ji Soo's grave

416
00:48:22,956 --> 00:48:26,995
and all the actresses who disappeared quietly.

417
00:48:29,201 --> 00:48:31,499
Because of them,

418
00:48:33,588 --> 00:48:36,379
I refuse to give up where I stand.

419
00:48:45,503 --> 00:48:47,932
I'll be right there next to you.

420
00:48:49,667 --> 00:48:52,057
Let's take this road side by side.

421
00:48:52,057 --> 00:48:54,417
After that,

422
00:48:54,417 --> 00:48:57,083
nobody will

423
00:48:57,083 --> 00:48:59,360
lay a finger on you.

424
00:49:03,834 --> 00:49:06,826
What makes you think you can keep me safe?

425
00:49:11,443 --> 00:49:13,250
At this moment,

426
00:49:13,250 --> 00:49:15,471
I'm just a hungry hound

427
00:49:15,471 --> 00:49:19,369
roaming free with no owner.

428
00:49:19,369 --> 00:49:21,377
I don't have a single thing to offer.

429
00:49:21,377 --> 00:49:24,052
I need a master who'll provide for me.

430
00:49:24,782 --> 00:49:26,721
And the one I want for that

431
00:49:27,458 --> 00:49:29,807
is you.

432
00:49:32,895 --> 00:49:36,105
You just need to remain beside me.

433
00:49:36,769 --> 00:49:40,078
Hold my hand, and down the line,

434
00:49:40,078 --> 00:49:43,279
once we hold genuine power,

435
00:49:45,046 --> 00:49:48,409
that becomes what you've earned.

436
00:49:49,325 --> 00:49:52,121
We can't do this without each other.

437
00:49:53,076 --> 00:49:54,951
Let's form a pact.

438
00:49:56,364 --> 00:50:00,755
Every secret of yours I've seen,

439
00:50:01,890 --> 00:50:04,550
I'll carry to my grave.

440
00:50:08,333 --> 00:50:10,473
Are you threatening me?

441
00:50:11,250 --> 00:50:13,351
It's a marriage proposal.

442
00:50:15,154 --> 00:50:16,813
I will

443
00:50:18,333 --> 00:50:20,692
be your accomplice.

444
00:50:32,905 --> 00:50:38,173
[Prosecutor Bang Tae Seop]

445
00:50:43,540 --> 00:50:47,631
[Criminal Case Records]

446
00:50:47,631 --> 00:50:51,424
[Arrest Warrant]

447
00:50:55,931 --> 00:50:57,687
In the end,

448
00:50:58,584 --> 00:51:02,312
Bang Tae Seop buried the truth

449
00:51:02,312 --> 00:51:04,777
[Case No. 2018-No-1087, Murder]
to keep Chu Sang Ah under his control.

450
00:51:14,584 --> 00:51:16,834
Jae Sang!

451
00:51:16,834 --> 00:51:19,326
Wait! Please, wait!

452
00:51:19,326 --> 00:51:21,125
Mom!

453
00:51:21,125 --> 00:51:22,333
- Jae Sang!
- Wait!

454
00:51:22,333 --> 00:51:25,000
- Mom!
- You didn't do this!

455
00:51:25,000 --> 00:51:28,250
- Mom!
- It wasn't you!

456
00:51:28,250 --> 00:51:31,596
Mom!

457
00:51:48,834 --> 00:51:51,532
No.

458
00:51:53,005 --> 00:51:55,036
There was

459
00:51:56,167 --> 00:51:59,004
no other way for me

460
00:51:59,004 --> 00:52:01,709
except to become a killer.

461
00:52:22,755 --> 00:52:25,417
So what you're saying is

462
00:52:25,417 --> 00:52:27,750
you knew Kwon Se Myeong was the true culprit

463
00:52:27,750 --> 00:52:29,396
and you covered it up?

464
00:52:29,396 --> 00:52:31,709
Yeah. Kwon Se Myeong did it.

465
00:52:31,709 --> 00:52:35,055
He pressured it from the top.
What could I have done?

466
00:52:35,055 --> 00:52:37,167
You think making a scene then would've made

467
00:52:37,167 --> 00:52:39,497
- any difference?
- Bang Tae Seop!

468
00:52:43,869 --> 00:52:46,115
I've kept the proof from that time.

469
00:52:46,115 --> 00:52:50,550
I've been saving it to bring down WR
at the right moment.

470
00:52:52,458 --> 00:52:55,547
You're just the same.

471
00:52:55,547 --> 00:52:59,309
Why did you keep this from me all these years?

472
00:52:59,309 --> 00:53:01,803
If you had revealed it at the time,

473
00:53:01,803 --> 00:53:03,764
I never would've married you. Am I wrong?

474
00:53:03,764 --> 00:53:06,516
Watch what you say.

475
00:53:06,516 --> 00:53:09,269
We're not at that point yet.

476
00:53:09,269 --> 00:53:11,483
Son of a bitch.

477
00:53:11,483 --> 00:53:12,917
Even if I'm the sort of garbage

478
00:53:12,917 --> 00:53:15,025
who pulled an innocent person into this

479
00:53:15,025 --> 00:53:17,667
and wrecked his life to keep myself alive,

480
00:53:17,667 --> 00:53:21,281
I've carried a heavy burden of guilt.

481
00:53:21,281 --> 00:53:23,292
Do you understand?

482
00:53:23,292 --> 00:53:25,786
Not one day!

483
00:53:25,786 --> 00:53:28,100
There wasn't a moment
I didn't remember that night.

484
00:53:28,100 --> 00:53:29,922
Damn it.

485
00:53:30,916 --> 00:53:36,262
Okay. Just settle down first.

486
00:53:39,876 --> 00:53:41,684
You

487
00:53:42,552 --> 00:53:45,583
only looked at me as a celebrity

488
00:53:45,583 --> 00:53:48,608
to exploit for your big plans.

489
00:53:58,834 --> 00:54:00,453
Yeah.

490
00:54:02,041 --> 00:54:03,706
I know.

491
00:54:09,792 --> 00:54:12,590
It's my fault for marrying a killer.

492
00:54:17,958 --> 00:54:19,722
Damn it...

493
00:54:23,125 --> 00:54:25,363
Son of a bitch.

494
00:55:58,750 --> 00:56:00,406
I know.

495
00:56:01,736 --> 00:56:04,577
It's my fault for marrying a killer.

496
00:56:20,043 --> 00:56:22,845
Hey! You okay?

497
00:56:25,715 --> 00:56:26,834
Are you hurt?

498
00:56:26,834 --> 00:56:28,917
Hey!

499
00:56:28,917 --> 00:56:30,335
What?

500
00:56:30,335 --> 00:56:32,219
She's the one who messed up.

501
00:56:40,958 --> 00:56:42,834
Are you okay?

502
00:56:42,834 --> 00:56:45,034
Are you hurt anywhere?

503
00:56:46,167 --> 00:56:48,333
[Chu Sang Ah, accused of killing Oh Kwang Jae]

504
00:56:48,333 --> 00:56:50,373
Isn't she Chu Sang Ah?

505
00:57:04,750 --> 00:57:07,305
[Chu Sang Ah's two faces... what is the truth?]

506
00:57:10,385 --> 00:57:17,163
[Chu Sang Ah, accused of killing Oh Kwang Jae]

507
00:58:31,167 --> 00:58:33,083
You think a woman with blood on her hands

508
00:58:33,083 --> 00:58:34,871
could actually amount to anything?

509
00:58:34,871 --> 00:58:36,451
I'm sorry.

510
00:58:36,451 --> 00:58:38,091
Please forgive me.

511
00:58:38,091 --> 00:58:40,691
You went through hell this whole time too?

512
00:58:40,691 --> 00:58:42,750
I won't go down alone.

513
00:58:42,750 --> 00:58:44,472
One wrong move on the Oh Kwang Jae case

514
00:58:44,472 --> 00:58:46,931
and our entire family is finished.

515
00:58:46,931 --> 00:58:48,051
What?

516
00:58:48,051 --> 00:58:50,911
Might this birthday be your final one?

517
00:58:50,911 --> 00:58:53,071
What I've kept hidden for all these years

518
00:58:53,071 --> 00:58:55,876
without ever using it

519
00:58:55,876 --> 00:58:58,542
is my trump card.
